Dear Fellow ACS Members,

As you may know, I'm one of two finalist candidates for ACS President-Elect=
 this year. I will be attending the national ACS meeting in Boston and look=
 forward to meeting as many of you as I can there.

Over the past few months, I've attended three regional ACS meetings and had=
 an opportunity to talk with quite a few of you.  Our discussions reinforce=
d to me that we're on the right track for addressing some of the issues mos=
t important to you: employment opportunities for the younger generation of =
scientists, skills development for senior scientists, and reversing the lon=
g-term decline in federal budgets for research.

I've learned a lot from my recent conversations with you, and I appreciate =
your passion for these issues. Let's continue the dialogue at the national =
meeting at a special session ACS has organized next week:

"Meet the Candidates for ACS President-Elect"
Monday, August 17, 1:00 - 4:00 p.m.
Boston Convention Center, North Lobby, Halls A & B1

I hope you can come by, meet me and Brian Balasz, and learn more about our =
respective visions for ACS.   If you can't meet me there, I will also be at=
 the following events:

Sunday

  *   Diversity Reception, 5-7 p.m., Sheraton, Independence
  *   International Welcoming Reception, 5:30-7:30 p.m., Sheraton, Back Bay=
 C/D

Monday

  *   Industrial Networking Reception, 6:30-7:30 p.m., Convention 258A
  *   SciMix - Poster Session, 8-10 p.m., BCEC, Hall C

Tuesday

  *   Women Chemists Luncheon, 12-1 p.m., Sheraton Republic A/B
  *   Henry Hill Reception, 5-7 p.m., Seaport Hotel Ballroom A/B
  *   LGBT Reception, 6-8 p.m., Seaport Hotel Ballroom C
  *   ChemLuminary Reception, 8-9 p.m., Weston Copely Place, Essex Ballroom

If we don't have a chance to connect in Boston, please feel free to send me=
 a note with your thoughts about ACS and let me know what you expect from a=
 President-Elect. More information on my background and expertise, my platf=
orm, and statements from those who have endorsed me is available at http://=
allisonacampbell.tumblr.com/.

Thank you very much, and I look forward to seeing you in Boston.

Allison


