<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"color:black">Dear Fellow ACS Members,=
 <o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Ta=
homa&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;color:black"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"color:black">As you may know, I&#8217=
;m one of two finalist candidates for ACS President-Elect this year. I will=
 be attending the national ACS meeting in Boston and look forward to meetin=
g as many of you as I can there.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"color:black"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span>=
</p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"color:black">Over the past few months=
, I&#8217;ve attended three regional ACS meetings and had an opportunity to=
 talk with quite a few of you.&nbsp; Our discussions reinforced to me that =
we&#8217;re on the right track for addressing some of
 the issues most important to you: employment opportunities for the younger=
 generation of scientists, skills development for senior scientists, and re=
versing the long-term decline in federal budgets for research.<o:p></o:p></=
span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Ta=
homa&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;color:black"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"color:black">I&#8217;ve learned a lot=
 from my recent conversations with you, and I appreciate your passion for t=
hese issues. Let&#8217;s continue the dialogue at the national meeting at a=
 special session ACS has organized next week:<o:p></o:p></span></p>
